# Excel engine rules

## Logic vs layout

- Business and scoring logic: `crawler/`, `pipeline/`, `rules/`.
- Workbook I/O, formatting, TOC, view state: `src/hype_frog/reporter/`.
- **Do not mutate pipeline data** (`main_data` / upstream row dicts) inside the reporter layer. Treat dictionaries as **read-only**.

## Priority

Treat **workbook integrity** and **client-safe XML** as highest priority. Prefer defensive openpyxl usage over shortcuts.

## String sanitization

- Sanitize **all** outgoing string cell values: strip **non-printable / control** characters; prevent formula/CSV injection (strip leading `=`, `+`, `-`, `@` where the codebase applies injection guards).
- Keep enforcement aligned across:
  - `src/hype_frog/pipeline/export.py`
  - `src/hype_frog/reporter/engine_io.py`
  - sheet writers under `src/hype_frog/reporter/sheets/`
- Never write raw strings that break worksheet XML or conditional-formatting assumptions.

## Ghost pane selection and freeze panes

- When clearing `freeze_panes`, clear **orphaned** `sheetView` selections (e.g. `worksheet.views.sheetView[0].selection = []` or equivalent safe pattern).
- **Ghost pane guard:** selections must match splits. If `xSplit == 0`, remove `topRight` / `bottomRight`; if `ySplit == 0`, remove `bottomLeft` / `bottomRight`; never `bottomRight` unless **both** splits exist.
- Central helpers include `sanitize_sheet_view_selection`, `apply_optimal_view_state`; guardrail orchestration in `src/hype_frog/reporter/engine_guardrails.py` — keep paths aligned when touching freezes or merges.

## Nuclear view-state guardrails

For sheets that are not **Main** or **Dashboard**, when the used grid is very small (`max_row` / `max_column` thresholds as in code), **disable** freeze panes and autofilter to avoid fragile client view state.

## Numeric conditional formatting

Do not inject **non-numeric strings** into columns governed by numeric conditional rules; use blank/`None` when unmeasured.

## TOC and hyperlinks

- **Table of Contents** must match tab names exactly; entries use descriptive labels and stable descriptions — keep `src/hype_frog/reporter/sheets/toc.py` and `src/hype_frog/reporter/engine_guardrails.py` consistent.
- Validate internal hyperlinks against **actual sheet names** and escaped single-quote rules when renaming sheets.

## Content Optimisation Hub — Action Required

- The **Action Required** column is **formula-driven** in `engine_rows.py`: `=IF(<On-Page Optimization Score> >= 85, "Complete", "Needs Copy")`. So the live ready literal is **`Complete`** (score ≥ 85) and the blocked literal is **`Needs Copy`** (score < 85).
- **Allowed literal set** (`engine_guardrails._ACTION_REQUIRED_ALLOWED`): **`Complete`**, **`Needs Copy`**, **`Needs Optimisation`**. `engine_guardrails.apply_action_required_guardrails` normalises legacy/free-text values (e.g. `Ready to Publish`, `completed` → `Complete`; `Needs Optimization` → `Needs Optimisation`; unknown text → `Needs Copy`) and **skips the `Content Optimisation Hub` sheet**, which relies on the conditional rules below instead.
- **Conditional formatting** (`reporter/sheets/conditional.py` `apply_content_hub_conditional_rules`) highlights **`Needs Copy`** in **red** (white bold), **`Needs Optimisation`** in amber, and **`Complete`** / `Ready to Publish` in green via `CellIsRule`. Do not rename literals without updating both the formula and the format rules.
- **Status** is a separate workflow column (data-validation list `To Do, In Progress, Review, Completed`); Dashboard completion metrics count `Status == Completed`, not Action Required.
- Do not pass **`None`** to action columns where populated text is required for formatting.

## Reporter module ownership

- `engine_guardrails.py` — invariants (Action Required normalisation, TOC refresh, freeze policy, tooltips).
- `engine_formatting.py` — visual formatting and conditional formats.
- `engine_io.py` — workbook-safe I/O, sanitization, row-writing bridges.
- `engine_rows.py` — report-row assembly and domain-specific shaping.
- `excel_engine.py` — compatibility facade / re-export, not the behaviour monolith.
- `narrative_engine.py` — generates natural-language insight copy for sheet cells. Read-only consumer of row dicts; no workbook writes.
- `summary_builder.py` — aggregates cross-sheet summary statistics consumed by the Dashboard and Executive Dashboard. No workbook writes.
- `dashboard_logic.py` — computes Dashboard KPI values and chart data from assembled rows. No workbook writes; callers in `sheets/dashboard.py` own actual worksheet writes.
- `chart_compat.py` — openpyxl chart compatibility shims. Isolated here so chart-specific workarounds do not leak into other writers.
- `workbook_audit.py` — post-write audit pass that validates workbook state (TOC alignment, sheet name collisions, formula integrity). **Read-only** against the workbook — must not modify cells; raise or log issues only.
- `pdf_exporter.py` — generates a PDF executive report when `HF_EXPORT_PDF=1`. Generation is **non-fatal**: failures log at `WARNING` and do not block xlsx or HTML delivery. See PDF env vars below.
- `help_layer.py` — injects tooltip / comment overlays into sheets. Runs after all data writes; never writes data cells.
- `sheets/config.py` — sheet-level constants (column widths, row heights, colour palettes) shared across sheet builders. No logic.

## New sheets

When adding a sheet: update **TOC** (`workbook_layout.py` tab order + `engine_guardrails.friendly_toc_description`), apply **view-state** guardrails, run **sanitization** on written rows. Merged builders live in `reporter/sheets/merged_builders.py`.

## Link Inventory deduplication

Dedup key: `(Source URL, Target URL, Anchor Text)` in `build_link_inventory_rows`.

## Main sheet conditional formatting

`apply_main_sheet_heatmaps` in `conditional.py` — 0–100 colour scales on `SEO Health Score`, `Mobile/Desktop PSI Score`, Lighthouse category scores and `AEO Readiness Score`; inverted scale on `Lab LCP (Mobile) (s)`; 0/5/10 scale on `E-E-A-T Signal Score`; a `Word Count (Body)` data bar; and `CellIsRule` fills (e.g. `Status Code` ≥ 400 red). Respect `HF_DISABLE_CONDITIONAL_FORMATTING`.

## HTML executive report modules

Modules under `reporter/` for the white-label HTML executive report:

- `html_report_data.py` — HTML report data aggregation; read-only consumer of pipeline row dicts. Produces a `ReportContext` dataclass.
- `html_report_renderer.py` — HTML template rendering; pure string transformation, no I/O.
- `html_report_writer.py` — HTML file I/O; writes rendered HTML to disk.
- `mocha_theme.py` — Catppuccin Mocha palette, HTML CSS helpers, Excel palette overrides (`HF_REPORT_THEME` / `HF_EXCEL_THEME`).

Triggered by `HF_EXPORT_HTML=1`. Generation is **non-fatal** — failures log at `WARNING` and do not block xlsx delivery.

**HTML report env vars** (all optional):
- `HF_EXPORT_HTML=1` — enable HTML report generation.
- `HF_REPORT_THEME=mocha` — dark Catppuccin Mocha layout + JetBrains Mono (Google Fonts). Default theme is light/self-contained (no CDN).
- `HF_REPORT_PREPARED_BY` — preparer name shown in report header.
- `HF_REPORT_CLIENT_NAME` — client name shown in report header and footer.
- `HF_REPORT_LOGO_PATH` — path to logo image embedded as base64 in the HTML.
- `HF_REPORT_BRAND_COLOUR` — hex colour for primary brand elements (default `#1e293b`; mocha default `#1e1e2e`).
- `HF_REPORT_ACCENT_COLOUR` — hex colour for accent/CTA elements (default `#2563eb`; mocha default `#94e2d5`).

**Excel theme env var:**
- `HF_EXCEL_THEME=mocha` — swap canonical RAG/heatmap constants in `sheets/config.py` to mocha-inspired values at import time.

Canonical palette tables: [`docs/excel_reporting_standards.md`](../../docs/excel_reporting_standards.md).

## PDF executive report

Triggered by `HF_EXPORT_PDF=1`. Generation is **non-fatal** — failures log at `WARNING` and do not block xlsx or HTML delivery.

**PDF env vars** (all optional):
- `HF_EXPORT_PDF=1` — enable PDF report generation.
- `HF_PDF_CLIENT_NAME` — client name shown in report.
- `HF_PDF_LOGO_PATH` — path to logo image.
- `HF_PDF_PREPARED_BY` — preparer name.
- `HF_PDF_BRAND_COLOUR` — hex colour for primary brand elements (default `#1e293b`).

All env vars above must be documented in `.env.example` whenever they change.

## Duplicate column prevention

Use `header_exists_in_worksheet` before inserting navigation headers such as **BACK TO DASHBOARD**.

## Testing touchpoints

After changing view state, TOC, or conditional formatting, run pytest (`test_excel_engine.py` and related tests under `tests/`).
